GRUB 2 bootloader configuration.

.SH BOOT SEQUENCE
.PP
.nf
BIOS/UEFI → GRUB 2 (custom mOSs theme)
    → Linux 6.6 kernel (silent, loglevel=3)
    → /init (custom PID-1 shell script)
        → mount proc/sys/dev/run/tmp
        → mdev -s  (device population)
        → modprobe GPU / input / sound drivers
        → moss-bridge --daemonize
        → aplay chime.mp3 (async)
        → setsid /bin/moss-shell </dev/tty1 >/dev/tty1
            → boot splash (eye ASCII + module loader)
            → login screen
            → terminal or wm mode
.fi

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MOSS_BRIDGE_SOCK
Override the bridge socket path.
.TP
.B MOSS_CONFIG
Override the config file path.
.TP
.B TERM
Must be a colour-capable terminal (e.g., xterm-256color).
.TP
.B MOSS_MODE
Set to
.I compositor
in kernel cmdline to launch Wayland compositor instead of ncurses shell.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Normal exit.
.TP
.B 1
Initialisation failure (terminal unavailable, bridge not running).

